                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 511. 4A1/916</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Schuyler</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-11-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 15, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Schuyler says the Government of Japan has no objection to substance of opium
                    proposal, but reserve their views, and would like to know date of conference
                    three months in advance.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
